page.title: 03A Historical Home
page.content: Our family live in an ancient house 206 years old called{Wood End {House.}When it was built the garage was a farmhouse which was built 114 years earlier. The people next door live in the converted barn which they have done up very nicely. The newest part of the house is made up of four cottages. The winduws are all widened mullions with sash frames. We have many rooms that an ordinary house doesn't have such as a washroom,study,cellar and a keeping room which is where we have a refrigerator and our freezers and food store. In our{garden}we have a stone summer house and a stone shed. The garden has two levels with some steps coming round. A drain along the west facing side turns and runs under the house.
